## Why This Is Asked
Tests nuanced DP on partitioning with range-dependent block costs, requiring problem decomposition, state design, and path reconstruction.

## Key Concepts
- DP over prefixes and block counts
- Efficient range max computation in transitions
- Path reconstruction via parent pointers

## Code Example
```javascript
function maxScore(nums, m) {
  const n = nums.length;
  const dp = Array.from({length: n+1}, ()=> Array(m+1).fill(-Infinity));
  const par = Array.from({length: n+1}, ()=> Array(m+1).fill(-1));
  dp[0][0] = 0;
  for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
    for (let t = 1; t <= Math.min(i, m); t++) {
      let curMax = -Infinity;
      for (let j = i-1; j >= t-1; j--) {
        curMax = Math.max(curMax, nums[j]);
        const val = dp[j][t-1] + curMax * (i - j);
        if (val > dp[i][t]) {
          dp[i][t] = val;
          par[i][t] = j;
        }
      }
    }
  }
  // Reconstruct endpoints
  const ends = [];
  let i = n, t = m;
  while (t > 0) {
    ends.push(i);
    i = par[i][t];
    t--;
  }
  return {score: dp[n][m], ends: ends.reverse()};
}
```

