## Why This Is Asked

Tests ability to design a DP over partitions where block value depends on both max and sum, plus reconstruction of segments. Encourages discussion on precomputation of range maxima and efficient transitions.

## Key Concepts

- DP over partitioning with fixed number of segments
- Block value using max and sum requires precomputation
- Path reconstruction for exact endpoints

## Code Example

```javascript
function maxBlockPartition(A, k){
  const n=A.length;
  const pref=new Array(n+1).fill(0);
  for(let i=0;i<n;i++) pref[i+1]=pref[i]+A[i];
  // precompute max for all subarrays
  const maxSub=Array.from({length:n},()=>Array(n).fill(0));
  for(let i=0;i<n;i++){ let m=A[i]; for(let j=i;j<n;j++){ m=Math.max(m,A[j]); maxSub[i][j]=m; } }
  const blockVal=(l,r)=> (r-l+1)*maxSub[l][r] - (pref[r+1]-pref[l]);
  const dp=Array.from({length:n+1},()=>Array(k+1).fill(-Infinity));
  const par=Array.from({length:n+1},()=>Array(k+1).fill(null));
  dp[0][0]=0;
  for(let i=1;i<=n;i++){
    for(let t=1;t<=k;t++){
      dp[i][t]=dp[i-1][t];
      par[i][t]=[i-1,t];
      for(let s=1;s<=i;s++){
        const val=dp[s-1][t-1] + blockVal(s-1,i-1);
        if(val>dp[i][t]){ dp[i][t]=val; par[i][t]=[s-1,t-1]; }
      }
    }
  }
  // reconstruction would backtrack from (n,k) using par
  return {best: dp[n][k], par};
}
```

