- How would you optimize to avoid O(n^2 k) in practice?  
- How does reconstruction behave with negative block values?

## Why This Is Asked
Tests counting paths with variable step lengths using DP, a common interview pattern in operations and logistics contexts.

## Key Concepts
- 1D DP for path counting
- Handling variable jump lengths
- Modulo arithmetic for large counts

## Code Example
```javascript
function countWays(jumps){
  const n = jumps.length;
  const MOD = 1000000007;
  const dp = new Array(n).fill(0);
  dp[0] = 1;
  for(let i = 0; i < n; i++){
    const maxJump = Math.min(jumps[i], n - 1 - i);
    for(let s = 1; s <= maxJump; s++){
      dp[i + s] = (dp[i + s] + dp[i]) % MOD;
    }
  }
  return dp[n - 1] || 0;
}
```

