- How does the solution adapt to different indexing conventions (1-based vs 0-based) and handle edge cases where n < 2k-1?
- What modifications are needed if we allow adjacent blocks or change the objective function?

## Why This Is Asked

This problem tests partitioning a sequence into exactly k blocks where block value is non-linear in length. It requires a careful DP with reconstruction and shows understanding of prefix sums and state transitions.

## Key Concepts

- DP over partitions
- Prefix sums for O(1) subarray sums
- Non-linear block value and reconstruction
- Time/space trade-offs: O(n^2 k) time, O(nk) space

## Code Example

