## Why This Is Asked
Tests 1D partition DP, median-based block costs, and reconstruction; mirrors realistic facility placement.

## Key Concepts
- DP over partitions
- Median-based block cost
- Prefix sums for O(1) block cost
- Backpointer reconstruction
- Time/space trade-offs and potential optimizations

## Code Example
```javascript
function minPostOffice(X, k) {
  const n = X.length;
  const cost = Array.from({length: n}, () => Array(n).fill(0));

  // Precompute prefix sums for O(1) range sum queries
  const prefix = new Array(n + 1).fill(0);
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {
    prefix[i + 1] = prefix[i] + X[i];
  }

  // Precompute block costs using median property
  for (let l = 0; l < n; l++) {
    for (let r = l; r < n; r++) {
      const m = Math.floor((l + r) / 2);
      cost[l][r] = (X[m] * (m - l) - (prefix[m] - prefix[l])) +
                   ((prefix[r + 1] - prefix[m + 1]) - X[m] * (r - m));
    }
  }

  // DP table and backpointers
  const dp = Array.from({length: n + 1}, () => Array(k + 1).fill(Infinity));
  const parent = Array.from({length: n + 1}, () => Array(k + 1).fill(-1));
  dp[0][0] = 0;

  for (let p = 1; p <= k; p++) {
    for (let i = 1; i <= n; i++) {
      for (let j = p - 1; j < i; j++) {
        const candidate = dp[j][p - 1] + cost[j][i - 1];
        if (candidate < dp[i][p]) {
          dp[i][p] = candidate;
          parent[i][p] = j;
        }
      }
    }
  }

  // Reconstruct solution
  const blocks = [];
  let curr = n;
  for (let p = k; p >= 1; p--) {
    const start = parent[curr][p];
    blocks.unshift([start, curr - 1]);
    curr = start;
  }

  return { cost: dp[n][k], blocks };
}
```

## Complexity Analysis
- Time: O(kn²) for DP transitions plus O(n²) for cost preprocessing
- Space: O(nk) for DP table, reducible to O(n) with layer optimization

## Why This Is Asked

Explores a novel variation of LPS with deletions, forcing a 3D DP and careful reconstruction.

## Key Concepts

- 3D DP: i, j bounds plus remaining deletions t.
- Transitions handle match, deletion of either end, and base cases.
- Reconstruction by tracing choices from dp[0][n-1][k].
- Space optimization via rolling t or two 2D layers.

## Code Example

```javascript
function maxLPSWithDeletions(s, k) {
  const n = s.length;
  const dp = Array.from({length: n}, () => Array.from({length: n}, () => Array(k+1).fill(0)));
  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) dp[i][i][0] = 1;
  for (let len = 2; len <= n; len++) {
    for (let i = 0; i + len - 1 < n; i++) {
      const j = i + len - 1;
      for (let t = 0; t <= k; t++) {
        if (s[i] === s[j]) {
          dp[i][j][t] = Math.max(dp[i][j][t], (i+1<=j-1? dp[i+1][j-1][t] : 0) + 2);
        }
        if (t > 0) {
          dp[i][j][t] = Math.max(dp[i][j][t], dp[i+1][j][t-1], dp[i][j-1][t-1]);
        }
      }
    }
  }
  return dp[0][n-1][k] || 0;
}
```

## Follow-up Questions

- How would you optimize to O(nk) space while preserving O(n^2 k) time?
- How does the solution change if deletions must be exactly k?

## Why This Is Asked

Tests a non-trivial DP over a linear sequence with a non-crossing constraint and reconstruction of the chosen pairs. It balances readability with the need to optimize across many left endpoints efficiently.

## Key Concepts

- Non-crossing pairings on a line
- DP by right endpoint with reconstruction
