Why This Is Asked

Tests DP for non-overlapping intervals with fixed cost and gaps, reflecting scheduling problems.

Key Concepts

- DP with dp[i][t] for first i days and t windows
- Prefix sums for quick window sums
- End-at-i transitions with a preceding gap
- Backpointers for reconstruction
- Time: O(n^2 k); Space: O(nk)

Code Example

```javascript
function maxProfitKWindows(A, k, c) {
  const n = A.length;
  const S = new Array(n+1).fill(0);
  for (let i=1;i<=n;i++) S[i] = S[i-1] + A[i-1];
  const dp = Array.from({length:n+1}, ()=> Array(k+1).fill(-Infinity));
  const prv = Array.from({length:n+1}, ()=> Array(k+1).fill(-1));
  dp[0][0] = 0;
  for (let i=1;i<=n;i++) {
    for (let t=0;t<=k;t++) {
      dp[i][t] = Math.max(dp[i][t], dp[i-1][t]);
      if (t>0) {
        for (let s=1;s<=i;s++) {
          if (i- s >= 2) {
            const val = dp[s-2][t-1] + (S[i]-S[s-1]) - c;
            if (val > dp[i][t]) { dp[i][t] = val; prv[i][t] = s; }
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
  // Reconstruction omitted for brevity
  return {best: dp[n][k], endIndex: n, t: k};
}
